freeText: Loved how clean the room was
Loved the hotel
Was nice that the room was all tidy and nice
As expected, the room was fine, no issues
The rooms ( we got the corner rooms with windows) were huge! The beds were great and the toiletries in the shower were high end!
everything was fine
Our room was clean as well as the entire hotel. The concierge on staff was excellent with telling us the must-sees and the must-nots.

The hotel was clean, and the staff was very knowledgeable and helpful. The roof top pool was amazing. The drink specials were wonderful. Close to everything. The beds were very comfortable. Will stay again.
Will be back soon!
person was nice (who checked us in)
The rooms were very comfortable and clean. Top notch hotel in all phases.
Very clean, traditional double room. Free wifi.
I got upgraded! Yay!
Hotel was very nice; very clean and comfortable beds.
Fast, easy. I really don't expect anything more
person at the front desk was talking to a friend - not working
The hotel has nice hot showers and clean comfortable beds. The rooms are clean and well appointed. I would recommend this hotel.
a really great value price coupled with no pet fee for two small dogs and so this was the choice for a four weeknights visit. Check in is easy and friendly

Myself and my boyfriend were here and decided to book this hotel due to its very affordable price, and oh my god am I happy we did! From the moment we stepped in we loved it. The receptionists were so lovely and helpful. Our room was amazing. Loved the modern look, which is quite rare as there are a lot of outdated hotels! The bar was brilliant.
We were greeted promptly and with a smile. The check-in process was easy and efficient.
Everything was good
GREAT hotel, a calming scent welcomes you in the lobby, refreshing drink awaits you blending with the calming scent
They're the nicest staff who are always willing to accommodate, for example upgrade.
Best hotel ever!
Best hotel in town
I asked a question at the front desk, the person clearly didn't want to do the 2 minutes of work to help me out
Good value for the money
Really nice hotel, great bar, great rooms. Really excellent location for night out and shopping.

My room was large & very comfortable. At night it was quiet, & the large window had a blind as well as black out curtains so it was dark! My bed was glorious, with wonderful sheets & pillows & perfect softness. In the morning my shower was fabulous.
This hotel is very lovely and wonderful.
The service from the front desk, lounge, dining areas and house keeping......all just cater to the guest on such a high level. Beyond our expectations every year.
The rooms and facilities are excellent - rooms are spacious and well appointed, with good soundproofing.

Attended a family wedding last weekend and can't say enough about this hotel !!
The staff was very attentive ...from the bar manager where we killed time til the reception started upstairs to the waitstaff for the event! Everyone was friendly and willing to ensure all guests were having a good time!
I asked about a dinner place, person just mumbled "everything around here is good". Not very helpful
Everyone said hi and was friendly
People seemed to enjoy being and working here

I called to get a early check in and was told I would be able to check in at 11am. I headed to the hotel after landing expecting to wait two hours. It's 4pm and I am still waiting for a room. And the manger doesn't care that I've been here in the lobby waiting. I was giving misinformation which had a huge impact on my trip with no concern. I would not recommend staying here!!!!!!

I had the worst experience with this hotel I have ever had in staying in hotels. The staff act like I owed them something for staying here. They were not frendly and acted if I was not a paying customer.
Was nice to come back from a long day and have someone say "hi"!
There is nothing about this hotel that I could recommend. I travelled for 30 years and this is probably the 3d worse hotel experience. Service at the front desk is pathetic.
Holy cow this was a terrible experience from the second we got there to the very end. This is the least hospitable hotel I've ever stayed at.
The people at the main desk were incredibly unfriendly... there for 3 full days not one friendly interaction.
Overpriced. Tiny rooms. Room was so bad and staff so rude that I paid for it and left preferring to stay anywhere else.
Very friendly person checked me in. Even looked for an upgraded room (but none was available)
Everyone was pleasant and helpful
Ultra-modern hotel with a very friendly and efficient staff.
Too expensive for what I got
Took way too long to check-in at the front desk
Need more people to improve checkin time
Pleasantly surprised spacious rooms updated features. We will look for the brand in our travels. The receptionist was very friendly and knowledgeable of the area.
Why can't the checkin process be streamlined
Excellent property. Rooms very quiet and nicely appointed. Staff was the very best - from the valet to the front desk personnel.
Place was ok, but not for what we paid
OMG - first impression not good - took 30 minutes to register
Terribly long wait to checkin
Facilities not worth the money
Why only 1 person to register???
The entire staff makes you feel at home when you visit this property. They are all willing to help and they do it with a smile. Great location.
This hotel is amazing. Love the rooms and the service.
This hotel exceeded our expectations. The staff is very friendly and always attentive to your needs.
The employees were awesome and very accommodating.

I already spoke to the concierge manager I believe at check out however, I am still not satisfied with the guest service that was given throughout my trip. My wife and I got there on Saturday evening and as we pulled up to valet, the guy was standing there talking to some girl that clearly didn't work there for about 20 minutes before even looking in our direction. Had to ask him what the process was and he said are you checking in? And didn't even explain the process. We weren't sure if we were to park ourselves or didn't even know that the hotel offered only valet. As we entered the two front desk agents were having a non work related conversation and didn't even bother to look over
The staff is very friendly and warm.

The staff were great, the room was very comfortable, could be tweaked just a little bit more as far as handicapped accessibility, but overall it's a Great place to stay and there are a lot of restaurant's around the area!
Special thanks goes out to Staff member Stu who was very friendly and helped us with local restaurant suggestions.

The biggest reason I am writing this review is due to a wonderful front desk employee - Pat!. I arrived at 10:30 pm plus and he was ever so friendly with a big smile, knew the answers to my questions, listened to my requests AND was as obliging as he could be. Two nights later I needed change and he literally remembered me! His personality, knowledge and attention to detail are a major plus for a person in his work position; I hope his immediate supervisor acknowledges this.
I was deeply offended by the treatment I experienced from two of the front desks women.
Great Location, friendly staff & Service was Excellent.
Staff at this hotel are at a level not seen at many hotels . they make you feel at home from the front desk to the bartender.

During check in I asked the woman at the desk if we could give her my boyfriends rewards number. Both of our names were on the reservation but they wouldn't let us use it, maybe because I put my card down when we were first reserving the room? He was staying in the room and paying for 2/3 of the nights. Made no sense why they wouldn't let him earn points for that. Woman at the main desk just rudely told us no and wouldn't try to figure it out what so ever.

The staff is very nice and accommodating, for example, we mentioned at check in that my daughter's I phone charger quit working and we asked for a suggestion on where we could buy another one for her. They offered that their store had them and it was only $10. That was great!
This place was too far from the center of town
When we fist walked in we were very disappointed and all we had seen was the front desk.

When we got there, we found the front desk staff trapped in corian-covered circular desk in a frenetic lobby. There was lots of activity and noise, but no seating. It was hardly a welcoming experience.
The resturant took too long and was way too expensive

When the best thing about a hotel room is that the toilet really flushes well, things are bad. Room had NO windows (never have seen that before).  Minimal and inadequate lighting, made worse by fact that multiple lights were not working. When maintenance came, he said they couldn't fix those lights (even though the hotel is less than 1 year old).
No newspapers, no cleaning of my room when asked.

The billing was a nightmare... not only was I overcharged $20 US every night over my coworkers charges with reservations made at the same time, my VISA was charged four times with four large amounts. The receipts were impossible to decipher. This is going to be a nightmare to get sorted!!!!!
Nobody cleaned my room
For the expensive charge this hotel was one of the absolute worse experiences I have had in all my travels.

my stay was very bad. the bed was the worst bed that i ever slept on. fire alarm went off from 1am till 4am with no apology from management. then at check out management tried to bait and switch my bill with a higher rate and proceed to argue that they were not trying to scam us. i would never recommend or stay at this  hotel ever again. i give this hotel 2 thumbs down.
This is definitely a terrible hotel for families to stay in, for a myriad of reasons I don't have enough room to list. Bed terrible. Too expensive. Bad Management!
The room wasn't as good as I aspected, in terms of the bathroom not being so clean
